1. Definitions
   - "Software" refers to the Asset Finder tool, including all source code, documentation, and associated files
   - "Author" refers to the original creator of the Asset Finder
   - "User" refers to any individual or entity using the Software
   - "Commercial Use" refers to any use of the Software in a commercial setting
   - "Independent Developer" refers to an individual or company with 5 or fewer employees AND annual revenue under $200,000

2. Personal Use License
   The Software is available for free personal use under the following conditions:
   a) Users may use, modify, and adapt the Software for personal projects
   b) Users may not redistribute modified versions of the Software
   c) Users may contribute improvements back to the original repository through pull requests
   d) Any modifications must be for personal use only

3. Commercial Use
   a) Commercial use of the Software in companies with more than 5 employees or 
      annual revenue exceeding $200,000 requires a valid license purchased through 
      the Unity Asset Store
   b) Independent Developers may use the Software for free, including for 
      commercial projects
   c) Each developer in a commercial setting requiring a paid license must have 
      their own license
   d) The Software may not be resold, redistributed, or included in other 
      commercial products
   e) Only the Author has the right to sell the Software through any marketplace

4. Contributions
   a) By submitting contributions to the Software's repository, contributors grant the Author
      permanent rights to include their contributions in both free and commercial versions
   b) Contributors maintain copyright of their contributions but may not sell them separately

5. Warranty Disclaimer
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED.
   THE AUTHOR SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING
   FROM THE USE OF THE SOFTWARE.

6. License Modifications
